TITLE: Russia accused of kidnapping head of Ukraine nuclear plant
SUMMARY: Russia has been accused of kidnapping the director general of the Zaporizhzhia nuclear power plant just moments after Putin signed a decree claiming the region.

TITLE: Iran attack kills 19, including 4 elite Revolutionary Guard members
SUMMARY: 19 people were killed on Friday after an attack on a southeastern police station, adding to the on-going aftermath in Iran following the death of Mahsa Amini, while in police custody.

TITLE: Ukraine war: Russia withdraws troops from Lyman, strategic town in region Putin annexed
SUMMARY: Ukraine's Armed Forces said it had encircled as many as 5,500 Russian troops near the town of Lyman in the Donetsk region.

TITLE: Ukraine 'more united than before' Russian invasion, journalism student says
SUMMARY: "It was a fight for survival," journalism student Elina Konavalyuk explained about living last winter in occupied Kherson, a city now in line for annexation into Russia.

TITLE: North Korea fires fourth ballistic missile in one week after Vice President Harris' gaffe
SUMMARY: North Korea fired its fourth ballistic missile in a week days after Vice President Kamala Harris accidentally said the U.S. was allied with the rogue state.

TITLE: Iranian authorities arrest celebrities, artists, foreign nationals during protest crackdown: report
SUMMARY: Iranian officials have accused foreign nations of whipping up the demonstrations through singers, artists, poets and celebrities, who have posted media in support of protestors.

TITLE: Myanmar's military government accuses rebel forces of shooting at passenger plane
SUMMARY: The Myanmar military government has accused rebel forces of shooting at a passenger plane in Kayah. One passenger was wounded when a bullet penetrated the plane's fuselage.

TITLE: Virus kills 100K cows and buffaloes in India, livelihoods threatened
SUMMARY: A viral outbreak in India has killed 100K cows and buffaloes and sickened another 2 million. The virus, known as lumpy skin disease, is spread through insects.

TITLE: Unlikely family? Cows in Germany adopt wild boar piglet
SUMMARY: A cow herd has taken in a lone wild boar piglet in Germany. The cattle farmer said the piglet, nicknamed Frieda, may have gotten separated from its group.

TITLE: EU wants European nations to crack down on visas for Russian citizens
SUMMARY: The European Union is asking the 27 nations within its jurisdiction to clamp down on issuing Russian citizens visas, as many Russians flee their home country amid a military draft.
